// Man page for swap
manSwap="SWAP(1)                          X Shell Manual                          SWAP(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    swap - Exchange two file names
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>swap</b> AFILE BFILE
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Atomic file name exchange utility. Swaps the names of two files without
    requiring temporary storage or leaving intermediate states. Useful for
    quick file replacement, testing scenarios, and maintaining file relationships
    during operations. Both files must exist and be accessible.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>AFILE BFILE</b>
    Swap names of two files
    AFILE becomes BFILE, BFILE becomes AFILE
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Basic Swap</color>
    <b>swap file1.txt file2.txt</b>
    Exchange file names

    <color=#e4ff34># Config Management</color>
    <b>swap config.bak config.conf</b>
    Restore backup config

    <b>swap app.new app.prod</b>
    Deploy new application

    <color=#e4ff34># Testing</color>
    <b>swap index.html index.test.html</b>
    Test new homepage

    <b>swap passwd passwd.old</b>
    Revert password file

    <color=#e4ff34># Binary Replacement</color>
    <b>swap /bin/ls /root/trojan_ls</b>
    Replace binary with trojan

    <b>swap sshd sshd_backdoor</b>
    Deploy backdoored daemon
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>mv</b>, <b>cp</b>, <b>ln</b>"